1. Add 2tbsp cocoa powder, 2 tbsp condensed milk and 1 tbsp of coconut oil to a bowl
2. Briefly mix together then add 1/2 cup of warmed milk (or milk subsitute)
3. Now mix the contents of the bowl well until the mixture thickens
4. Add in any toppings of choice (almonds, freeze dried strawberries...)
5. Move the mixture into molds or on a sheet pan and put in the freezer for 1 hour
6. Enjoy the tasty homemade treat!
